reviews.review: Bad acting, poorly developed storyline, this was one of the worst of the Star Wars movies. The Rise of Skywalker spent too much time worshiping princess Leia and again made a fool out of Luke. Palpatine's character was weak, uninteresting and cringe for the first time in any movie. Fynn was useless and unwatchable. The forced kiss scene between Rey and Ren was lame. I walked out of this movie very unsatisfied kinda like when you order a burger medium-rare from your favorite place but it comes out well done. Only at a burger place, you can always send it back. I can't unsee this lame movie, unfortunately.

If you ever want to enjoy a a Disney's Star Wars Film just know that their is no better example of efforts than TROS although the plot is weak and the story makes no sense for a Star Wars film, this film is an interesting failure but visually stunning and fantastic but the lack of story and characters was just poor. Darn Shame.

A mishmash of incoherent poorly explained(deus ex machina)if at all plot lines stitched together forcibly ,to create a mess of a film that tries to hide behind fast pace action to keep you from thinking and realizing how nonsensical it is. All this movie is, is a failed attempt by Disney to rectify what Kathleen Kennedy and Ryan Johnson did to the Star Wars franchise ,a mess of a film and a product of a room of executives who do not and will never understand the Star Wars Fandom ,a point proven by the ton of what they believed to be fan service infused into this film. This poorly produced film ties in perfectly with the other two that came before it thus concluding the end of what was a Trilogy that made Michael Bay look like a God of Cinematography and Direction.
All that had to be done was to create an original story that would not infringe and break the story we allready loved ,but somehow Disney has not only managed to wreck the old Characters we loved but also the new ones that we were eager to get to know and relate to ,a result of the poor if not inexistent character development. And now just watch the meaningless unsatisfying action and things we just pulled out of a hat and dont think

Disappointing. Lucas is missed. 
It's even worse than Episode I. Only above Episode VIII 
The good thing, Princess Leia does not fly in it. The bad, many script holes. The ugly, the waste of Lando's character, just like Luke's in episode VIII

Forget all the noise you heard about this movie being difficult to follow or packed with too much information. Those critics were probably stoned when they went into the theater. It was a great movie and definitely a MUST SEE, especially if you're a Star Wars fan.

Ignore the critics. I don't know what they're thinking. This installment of the Long Ago and Far Away Saga was very good ... I might even hazard to say great. I will see it again soon. As in every Star Wars movie, there's so much going on, I'm sure I'll notice new stuff with a second, or perhaps third, viewing. Of course, looking at Daisy Ridley makes nearly every moment a pleasure. If you're a Star Wars fan at all, you will enjoy The Rise of Skywalker.

The movie was great. I don’t know what some of those critics are on but I don’t want it. Fans and non-fans can easily get behind this movie. If you some what keep up with the lore of Star Wars across the shows and even books you will get a lot of gratification from the movie. Go in with an open mind and tempered expectations and you will enjoy the movie.

Not the worst "Star Wars" movie but very much the most disappointing, "The Rise of Skywalker" squanders almost every interesting choice afforded it by its two predecessors in favor of clumsy, rehashed fan service. This saga deserved a finale so much than the rushed, confusing, and superficial mishmash we got.
Up to like 2/3rds of the way through the movie was pretty good. Plot development had a nice place, a fair amount of action, and then it was just a big corny mess.
Lots of action, Lots of characters, Some surprise characters. Not much story
